
[1]averment

   AVER'MENT, n. [See Aver.]

   1. Affirmation; positive assertion; the act of averring.

   2. Verification; establishment by evidence.

   3. In pleading, an offer of either party to justify or prove what he
   alleges. In any stage of pleadings, when either party advances new
   matter, he avers it to be true, and concludes with these words, "and
   this he is ready to verify." This is called an averment.
